  "title": "Maintenance Engineer ",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Perform Preventive Maintenance.</li><li>Perform and attend to breakdowns calls and scheduled services.</li><li>Carry the hot line phone during OFF working hours, weekends and Public Holidays according to the schedule or when requested by the supervisor, and therefore attend to the breakdown calls during the silent hours, weekends and Public Holidays, according to the agreement in force with each client.</li><li>Work safely and with the safety equipments necessary to execute his duties. Work following the “Risk Management Guidelines” with concerns safety procedure and requirements.</li><li>Prepare accurately, clear and in due time service report for any intervention done.</li><li>Keep work place, tool box and tools in place, clean and tidy.</li><li>Prepare and submit monthly Time sheet.</li><li>Take responsibility for work done and follow up quotations.</li><li>Must know how to read electrical diagram (for equipment).</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Qualifications / Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in troubleshooting</li><li>Knowledge in PLC, Control is a plus</li><li>Professional Certificate or Diploma in electrical, electronic, mechatronics</li></ul><p><br /></p>",
